      "widgets_values": [
        "Narrator: This is the third time Kobayashi's mind has wandered today. The dim bar lights made his heart race, while the woman across the bar, her red lips slightly upturned, was gently tracing the rim of her glass with her fingertips.\nMature Woman: Little brother, interested in having a drink with your older sister?\nKobayashi: Huh? I...I...I'm actually not very good at drinking...\nNarrator: His fingers unconsciously gripped the rim of his glass, his Adam's apple bobbing up and down, as if something invisible was choking him.\nMature Woman: Can't drink? That's perfect—I'll teach you. This mojito is just the right amount of sweet, like the way you glanced at me just now.\nKobayashi: I...I didn't glance! ...Okay, I did glance. Just one glance!\nNarrator: He sat up abruptly, then immediately shrank back, as if those words had burned his lips.\nMature Woman: What's wrong? You're even trembling...Want to move closer? It's too noisy here.\nKobayashi: Move closer? \"But...but we've only just met...you don't even know me...\"\nMature Woman: Names don't matter, feelings do. ...And I feel...you're kind of cute.\nNarrator: Kobayashi's ears instantly turned bright red, even the little mole behind his ear seemed to be burning. He wanted to run away, but his feet felt like they were nailed to a bar stool.\nKobayashi: Cute? Nobody's ever said that to me...they all say I'm too boring, I can't even post on social media...\nMature Woman: So what about now? Dare to post something like—'Tonight, had a drink with a dangerous and charming older sister'?\nKobayashi: ...I don't even dare to choose a picture. Your smile is too...too lethal.\nMature Woman: Then don't post it. Some stories are only meant to be kept in the memories of two people—for example, are you planning to ask me to dance next?\nNarrator: He opened his mouth, but no sound came out. But this time, he didn't lower his head, but gently pushed away the untouched glass of soda and extended his hand to her.",
